The paper deals with the problem of phishing web page identification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach involves the use of visual descriptors to extract and classify visual features from web page screenshots, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. The use of machine learning models for image classification also indicates the involvement of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
